# $Header: /var/cvsroot/gentoo-x86/media-libs/libvorbis/ChangeLog,v 1.25 2004/01/14 22:07:16 gustavoz Exp $

  14 Jan 2004; <gustavoz@gentoo.org> libvorbis-1.0.1.ebuild:
  marked hppa

  14 Jan 2004; <gustavoz@gentoo.org> libvorbis-1.0.1.ebuild:
  added ~sparc

  26 Dec 2003; Martin Holzer <mholzer@gentoo.org> libvorbis-1.0.1.ebuild:
  Fixing syntax to not apply with gcc2. Closes 36451

  18 Dec 2003; Martin Holzer <mholzer@gentoo.org> libvorbis-1.0.1.ebuild:
  marking stable.

*libvorbis-1.0.1 (22 Nov 2003)

  22 Nov 2003; Brandon Low <lostlogic@gentoo.org> libvorbis-1.0.1.ebuild:
  Bump, had to remove both of the patches, this probably means that it doesn't
  use SIMD properly now, hopefully we'll get a new patch for this version at
  some point

  20 Nov 2003; Martin Holzer <mholzer@gentoo.org> libvorbis-1.0-r4.ebuild:
  marking stable. Closes #33925.

  14 Nov 2003; Aron Griffis <agriffis@gentoo.org> libvorbis-1.0-r2.ebuild:
  Stable on ia64

*libvorbis-1.0-r4 (11 Aug 2003)

  13 Dec 2003; Guy Martin <gmsoft@gentoo.org> libvorbis-1.0-r4.ebuild :
  Marked stable on hppa.

  04 Nov 2003; Joshua Kinard <kumba@gentoo.org> libvorbis-1.0-r4.ebuild:
  Added ~mips to KEYWORDS

  20 Sep 2003; jje <jje@gentoo.org> libvorbis-1.0-r4.ebuild:
  Filtering -msse2. Closes #28439.

  16 Aug 2003; jje <jje@gentoo.org> libvorbis-1.0-r4.ebuild:
  Filter -march=pentium?. See bug #26463.

  12 Aug 2003; jje <jje@gentoo.org> libvorbis-1.0-r4.ebuild:
  Fix simd_3dn flag (was simd-3dn.)

  11 Aug 2003; jje <jje@gentoo.org> libvorbis-1.0-r4.ebuild:
  More fun with simd patch. Now add -Dsimd-3dn if 3dnow. #26242.
  
  Also, filter -fomit-frame-pointer for k6 arches. #26239.

  05 Aug 2003; jje <jje@gentoo.org> libvorbis-1.0-r1.ebuild,
  libvorbis-1.0-r2.ebuild, libvorbis-1.0.ebuild, files/libvorbis-1.0-m4.patch,
  files/libvorbis-1.0-r2-m4.patch:
  New simd patch (use sse) and some clean out of old builds.
  
  Submitted by: Chris Gianelloni <wolf31o2@gentoo.org>

*libvorbis-1.0-r2 (12 Mar 2003)

  04 Jul 2003; Guy Martin <gmsoft@gentoo.org> libvorbis-1.0-r2.ebuild :
  Added hppa to KEYWORDS.

  12 Mar 2003; Martin Holzer <mholzer@gentoo.org> libvorbis-1.0-r2.ebuild,
  files/libvorbis-1.0-r2-m4.patch:
  Added symblink to file .so.0 for libvorbisfile and libvorbisenc. Also known as
  libvorbis-compat in other distros. Closes #15798.

  06 Dec 2002; Rodney Rees <manson@gentoo.org> : changed sparc ~sparc keywords
 
*libvorbis-1.0-r1 (13 Sep 2002)

  15 Dec 2002; Bjoern Brauel <bjb@gentoo.org> libvorbis-1.0-r1.ebuild :
  unmask on alpha

  13 Sep 2002; Brandon Low <lostlogic@gentoo.org> libvorbis-1.0-r1.ebuild :

  m4 fixes thanks to gentoo@liquidx.net (Alastair Tse) closes bug 6134.

*libvorbis-1.0 (19 Jul 2002)

  19 Jul 2002; Brandon Low <lostlogic@gentoo.org> libvorbis-1.0.ebuild :

  Well the vorbis folks have released 1.0, so here is our ebuild, enjoy!

*libvorbis-1.0_rc3-r2 (30 Mar 2002)

  30 Jun 2002; Martin Schlemmer <azarah@gentoo.org> libvorbis-1.0_rc3-r2.ebuild :
  The new patched gcc-2.95.3-r7 dont handle the "-mno-ieee-fp" flag gracefully.

*libvorbis-1.0_rc3-r1 (21 Mar 2002)

  21 Mar 2002; Seemant Kulleen <seemant@gentoo.org>  libvorbis-1.0_rc3-r1.ebuild :

  HTML documentation no longer gzipped.  It is now readable. This bug reported
  by stefan@mdy.univie.ac.at 


*libvorbis-1.0_rc3 (1 Feb 2002)

  1 Feb 2002; G.Bevin <gbevin@gentoo.org> ChangeLog :
  
  Added initial ChangeLog which should be updated whenever the package is
  updated in any way. This changelog is targetted to users. This means that the
  comments should well explained and written in clean English. The details about
  writing correct changelogs are explained in the skel.ChangeLog file which you
  can find in the root directory of the portage repository.
